','','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(258,2012,'Dave Livermore','N','','','','','2026-06-24 13:24:16','Dave Livermore is a candidate for Isabella County Road Commissioner (6-year term) on the 2026 ballot, who filed April 6, 2026. He is from Weidman, Michigan, and the Isabella County Road Commission is among the rural commissions involved with the Rural Roads Alliance of Michigan formed in late 2025.','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(259,14601,'Thomas Wiles','D','','','','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','Thomas Wiles is a Democratic candidate for an Alpine Township (Kent County) Board of Trustees seat, a partial term expiring 11/20/2028, on the August 4, 2026 primary ballot. He resides in Comstock Park. No campaign website or contact information was found online.','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(260,2381,'Otto B. McNaughton, IV.','D','','','(616) 691-8450','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','Otto B. McNaughton IV is the incumbent Grattan Township (Kent County) Clerk and is running for re-election in 2026 as a Democrat. He has handled township clerk duties including election administration and zoning matters. The listed phone is the Grattan Township office number, not a dedicated campaign line.','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(261,5090,'Kelsey Perdue','N','https://www.perdueforyou.com/','','','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','Kelsey Perdue is the incumbent Grand Rapids 3rd Ward City Commissioner, first elected in 2022 (defeating Kenneth Hoskins), and is running for re-election in 2026 with a campaign site at perdueforyou.com. She is a public-health leader whose work focuses on housing, economic development, and public safety, and is noted as the second Black woman elected to the Grand Rapids commission.','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(262,5124,'Elaina A Huizenga-Chase','N','','','','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','Elaina Huizenga-Chase is a 2026 candidate for Mayor of the City of Walker (Kent County) and reportedly the only person to file for the seat. She currently serves as Walker\'s Mayor Pro Tem and 3rd Ward City Commissioner, and is the daughter of former Walker Mayor and current state Senator Mark Huizenga.','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(263,5127,'John McCrackin','N','','','','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','John McCrackin is a 2026 candidate for the City of Walker (Kent County) Ward 2 City Commission seat. No campaign website or contact information was found online.','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(264,5128,'Terry Schweitzer','N','','','','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','Terry Schweitzer is a 2026 candidate for the City of Walker (Kent County) Ward 3 City Commission seat. No campaign website or contact information was found online.','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(265,8690,'Diana Kay Durst','N','','','','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(266,6981,'April Patin','N','','','','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(267,7009,'Nick Brock','N','','','','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(268,8798,'Brittney R. Rocha','N','','','','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','Brittney R. Rocha is a trustee on the Kelloggsville Public Schools Board of Education in Kent County, Michigan, running in 2026. Professionally she is a Legal Department Manager and attorney at Velo Law Office and has previously worked as a policy advisor and legislative director in the Michigan State Senate.','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(269,7050,'Jake Conway','N','','','','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','Jake Conway is a candidate for the Northview Public Schools Board of Education in Kent County, Michigan. He previously ran in the November 2024 special general election for the Northview board\'s at-large seat.','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(270,14655,'Phil Green','D','','','','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(271,13635,'Dan Beatty','D','','beatty.business@gmail.com','(313) 598-8945','','2026-06-24 13:24:17','Dan Beatty is a Democratic candidate for Trustee of Brighton Charter Township in Livingston County, Michigan, running for a partial term ending November 20, 2028, in the August 4, 2026 primary. He filed on April 21, 2026.','',0,'jon-uncon',''),(272,13636,'Ty T. 